# Release-gate rule

GitHub Actions is **disabled** at the repository level for this project.
The local release gate is the only gate. The canonical interfaces are
`just <target>` (preferred) and `make <target>` (fallback). The
gate-related targets (`gate-fast`, `gate-no-nightly`, `gate`) call into
`scripts/local_release_gate.sh`. Tooling pins are strict:
`cargo-audit 0.22.1`, `cargo-deny 0.19.4`, `zizmor 1.24.1`.

## When to run what

Pick the smallest sufficient check from this table for the inner edit-test
loop. The full `just gate` is mandatory before push and before reporting
work as done.

| Edit scope                                                  | Inner-loop                                              |
| ----------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------- |
| Pure docs (`*.md`, `docs/**`)                               | none (run `just gate-fast` before commit)               |
| `src/proof.rs`                                              | `just proof-tests`                                      |
| `src/vanillastark/**`                                       | `just vanillastark-tests`                               |
| `src/stwo_backend/**`                                       | `just lib`                                              |
| `src/bin/tvm.rs`                                            | `just gate-fast` then `just integration`                |
| `tests/**`                                                  | `cargo test --release --test <touched-name>`            |
| `programs/**` (`.tvm`)                                      | `just integration`                                      |
| `Cargo.toml` / `Cargo.lock` / `deny.toml` / `vendor/**`     | `just deps`                                             |
| `scripts/**.sh`                                             | `just shellcheck`                                       |
| `.github/workflows/**`                                      | `just zizmor`                                           |
| `Justfile` / `Makefile` / `scripts/local_release_gate.sh`   | `just gate-no-nightly`                                  |

For any change that touches the proof-system surface (claim metadata, AIR,
FRI, Merkle, transcript, or Stwo wiring), also add or update at least one
negative / tamper-path test, then run `just gate` before reporting done.

## Required before push

1. `just gate` exits 0.
2. The change is on a feature branch (not directly on `main`); a pull
   request will be opened before merge so AI commenters fire. Review
   approval and signed commits are not required.

## Forbidden

- Pushing directly to `main` (the ruleset blocks it).
- Editing `Cargo.lock` by hand.
- Adding a `.tvm` fixture under `programs/` whose name implies a model
  family it does not faithfully implement (see
  `docs/engineering/release-gates/naming-honesty.md`).
- Re-enabling a workflow under `.github/workflows/` without first
  re-enabling Actions per
  `docs/engineering/release-gates/local-only-policy.md`.

